description: Abandoned safari gear, including a pith helmet, camera, and glasses, lies on the ground next to a magazine titled "SAFARI SEE WILD ANIMALS UP CLOSE!". Large footprints with toe pads are visible in the earth nearby, leading towards a tree with a gaping hole in its base. The scene presents a dark irony, suggesting the photographer perhaps got too close to the wild animals advertised, with the large footprints hinting at their final encounter.

other_text.text: SAFARI SEE WILD ANIMALS UP CLOSE!
